qas.question: What was Oda Nobunaga's full name?

answers.text: a title of vice-governor of Kazusa province
an adult name (nanori) given at genpuku, the coming of age ceremony

context: For example, the full name of Oda Nobunaga would be "<a0_0>Oda Kazusanosuke Saburo Nobunaga<a0_0/>" (織田上総介三郎信長), in which "Oda" is <a1_0>a clan or family name<a1_0/>, "Kazusanosuke" is <a2_0>a title of vice-governor of Kazusa province<a2_0/>, "Saburo" is <a3_0>a formal nickname (yobina)<a3_0/>, and "Nobunaga" is <a4_0>an adult name (nanori) given at genpuku, the coming of age ceremony<a4_0/>. A man was addressed by his family name and his title, or by his yobina if he did not have a title. However, the nanori was a private name that could be used by only a very few, including the Emperor.
